Key Match Events: Pete Alonso hit a laser home run to right field in the second inning.
Brandon Pfaadt committed an error in the fifth inning, leading to two unearned runs.
Jordan Montgomery made his debut out of the bullpen and pitched the next four innings without giving up any runs.
Sean Manaea struck out 11 batters in the seventh inning.
Post-Match Reflections: Manager Torey Lovullo emphasized the importance of avoiding extra outs and making plays in key situations.
Brandon Pfaadt struggled in his start, giving up eight runs and failing to locate his fastball.
Eduardo Rodriguez will start for the Diamondbacks in the next game.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Diamondbacks avoided a shutout in the seventh inning with a Lourdes Gurriel Jr. solo homer and a Corbin Carroll two-run home run.
Jordan Montgomery performed well in his debut out of the bullpen, striking out two and limiting hits and walks.
